<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4425] Short command in Gogo Shell not working with Java 8 </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4425</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The bug comes from the different interpretation of String.split() method in line 474 of org.apache.felix.gogo.options.Options (in Gogo Shell).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the different results of the split method:&lt;br/&gt;
String val = &quot;-k&quot;.substring(1).split(&quot;&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
Java &amp;lt; 8:&lt;br/&gt;
val&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;=&quot;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
val&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;=&quot;k&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Java 8: &lt;br/&gt;
val&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;=&quot;k&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple fix can be an iteration of the characters instead of using split().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
